===Etymology===
Portuguese '''Formosa''' ("[[beautiful]]") < Latin '''[[formosus]]''' ("beautifully formed"), from '''[[forma]]''' ("form", "shape") + the adjective suffix '''[[-osus]]''' ("full of") (cf. English ''[[shapely]]'').

===Proper noun===
'''Formosa'''

# The name given to the province of [[Taiwan]] by the [[Portuguese]] colonists in the 16th century.

